side our domain.\n    36→\n    37→3. **Filter(Union) → filtered candidate list**\n    38→   - For each product in the unified pool:\n    39→     - Investigate its **launch / first public release date** from credible public info\n    40→       (official site, launch post, Product Hunt / HN launch, blog, press, etc.).\n    41→     - Decide if it satisfies **both**:\n    42→       1) Launch date is within the last **14 days** (relative to “today”).\n    43→       2) Product is clearly related to **AI coding / code agents / IDE / dev workflows**.\n    44→   - If you cannot reasonably verify that the launch is within 14 days,\n    45→     **treat it as NOT valid** and exclude it.\n    46→   - Internally keep, for each surviving product:\n    47→     - `release_date` in `YYYY-MM-DD` format (best reasonable guess)\n    48→     - short one-line justification (do not put the justification in final YAML).\n    49→\n    50→4. **Sort(filtered candidates) → final ordered list**\n    51→   - Only work with products that passed the filter.\n    52→   - Rank them by a simple mental score combining:\n    53→     - **recency** (more recent launch date is better),\n    54→     - **attention** (strong launch signal: PH upvotes, HN discussion, X/Reddit buzz),\n    55→     - **relevance** (how closely it fits “AI coding agent / IDE / devtool”).\n    56→   - You do not need to show the numeric score, just use it to order the list.\n    57→\n    58→\n    59→### Claude Code / todo-style planning requirements\n    60→\n    61→When running inside Claude Code with access to a `todowrite` (or similar TODO-list) tool,\n    62→you MUST first externalize this plan as an explicit TODO list **before** doing any research.\n    63→\n    64→Follow these rules:\n    65→\n    66→0. Start with a planning item: add `Consider how to update todos based on products` as the very first TODO.\n    67→\n    68→1. Based on the QUESTION list in the `user:` section, use the `todowrite` tool to create **one TODO item