e\": \"Devin's ARR growth from $1M to $73M in 9 months demonstrates strong market demand\",\n        \"source\": \"Business analysis February 2026\",\n        \"sentiment\": \"positive\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"quote\": \"Enterprise adoption at major financial institutions validates autonomous AI software engineer model\",\n        \"source\": \"Industry observers\",\n        \"sentiment\": \"positive\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"productName\": \"GitHub Copilot\",\n    \"title\": \"Multi-Model Integration with Claude and Codex AI\",\n    \"description\": \"GitHub announced integration of Claude and Codex AI directly into their platform on February 5, 2026, available to GitHub Copilot Pro Plus and Enterprise subscribers. Can be used in GitHub web, mobile app, and Visual Studio Code. Microsoft is also expanding internal testing of Claude Code for comparison with GitHub Copilot. This marks a shift from OpenAI-only dependency to supporting multiple AI providers.\",\n    \"updateType\": \"announcement\",\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/features/copilot\",\n    \"date\": \"2026-02-05\",\n    \"community_feedback\": [\n      {\n        \"quote\": \"GitHub Copilot wins on usage limits and parallel project support compared to some alternatives\",\n        \"source\": \"Developer comparison from 58 developers\",\n        \"sentiment\": \"positive\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"quote\": \"Code quality is comparable between GitHub Copilot and Claude Code according to user tests\",\n        \"source\": \"Developer feedback\",\n        \"sentiment\": \"neutral\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n]\n",
